modules.description: Converts runtime errors to strings, manages monadic operations, and performs file system tasks like reading, writing, and checking file existence. Works with custom error types, monadic structures, and path representations. Executes shell commands, logs messages at different levels, and retrieves file metadata such as modification time and directory contents.

Provides functions to manage and execute build processes, including initializing a development environment and triggering builds. Operates with configuration files and project directories. Used to set up isolated OCaml projects and compile them efficiently.

Handles error conversion, monadic workflows, and file system interactions, including reading, writing, and metadata retrieval. Supports custom error types, path manipulation, and shell command execution with logging capabilities. Processes file existence checks, modification times, and directory listings. Enables robust file management and system interaction within a monadic framework.
